
Overview of noun whiteness

The noun whiteness has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) white, whiteness -- (the quality or state of the achromatic color of greatest lightness (bearing the least resemblance to black))
2. purity, pureness, sinlessness, innocence, whiteness -- (the state of being unsullied by sin or moral wrong; lacking a knowledge of evil)
3. whiteness -- (lightness or fairness of complexion; "only the whiteness of her cheeks gave any indication of the stress from which she was suffering")
